critical_negative: I think for the most part it was good but there were some parts where we hit the end of a particular topic and we had to kind of work to get back into a flow.    There were also some parts where I basically had an awkward moment because I basically assumed that she was perhaps not from the US- which turned out to be correct but it was somewhat rude.  I was confused at time if this study was restricted to US or not, I know prolific is based in UK.  It didn't matter, we recovered and I didn't intend it that way but it was probably somewhat of a rude assumption.   She also started the conversation asking where I was from, which put me off a bit because usually people only ask where am I... not where I'm from.    She was younger than me too and was aware of that, so I think that might've caused some communication differences (particularly regarding the importance of where you are from).
